\par\plain {\f1\fs36\b0\i0\cf3 About This Template}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 By default, when compiled (File > Compile), this project will generate a document in the standard manuscript format for novels. Settings are also provided to make it easy to compile to a paperback-style PDF for self-publishing or an EPUB or Kindle ebook.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f1\fs36\b0\i0\cf3 How To Use This Template}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Inside the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Manuscript\u8221\'94 folder, create a new folder for each part of your novel as direct subdocuments of the Manuscript folder. Two  folders have already been created at this level for you, with the placeholder title \u8220\'93Part\u8221\'94. You should rename these with the titles of the parts of your novel.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-1440\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i1\cf1	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8259\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 Note}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 : The \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Manuscript\u8221\'94 folder is what we refer to in the documentation as the \u8220\'93Draft folder\u8221\'94. It\u8217\'92s just been renamed \u8220\'93Manuscript\u8221\'94 in this template.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Create a new folder for each chapter inside the relevant \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Part\u8221\'94 folder and title each folder with the name of the chapter. If you don\u8217\'92t intend to use chapter names, just use something descriptive that tells you what the chapter is about. (You do not need to\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 and indeed shouldn\u8217\'92t\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 title the folders \u8220\'93Chapter One\u8221\'94 and so on, because chapter numbering will be taken care of automatically during the Compile process.) The first chapter folder has been created for you with the placeholder title \u8220\'93Chapter\u8221\'94.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Create a new text document for each scene inside the chapter folders. (Upon export, scenes will be separated with the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93#\u8221\'94 character for standard manuscript format, or with a blank line for other formats.)}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Information about characters can be placed in the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Characters\u8221\'94 folder, and information about locations can be placed in the \u8220\'93Places\u8221\'94 folder. (These are just regular folders that have had custom icons assigned to them using the Documents > Change Icon feature.)}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Character and setting sketch sheets have been provided which can be used for filling out information about the people and places in your novel. These are located in the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Template Sheets\u8221\'94 folder.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-1440\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl1{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8259\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You should not edit the documents in the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Template Sheets\u8221\'94 folder directly unless you wish to change the templates (which you are free to do\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 you may wish to customise the sketch sheets or get rid of them entirely).}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8259\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 To create a new character sheet, click on the Characters folder (or wherever you want to create your new character sheet) and from the Project menu, select New From Template > Character Sketch. This creates a new character sketch document for you to edit and fill in with your character details. You can create setting sketch sheets in the same way.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8259\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Alternatively, you can just click \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Add\u8221\'94, or hit cmd-N, with the Characters or Places folders selected.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8259\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You can view character and setting sketches in the Inspector as follows:}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\fi-2160\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl2{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	1.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Select the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Bookmarks\u8221\'94 pane in the Inspector.}
\par\plain \ilvl2{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	2.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 If necessary, click on \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Document Bookmarks\u8221\'94 at the top and switch to \u8220\'93Project Bookmarks\u8221\'94.}
\par\plain \ilvl2{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	3.	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Click on the chevron next to the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Characters\u8221\'94 or \u8220\'93Places\u8221\'94 folders in the Bookmarks list and choose the sheet you wish to view. (Note that only folders with content show chevrons.)}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Notes\u8221\'94 folder has been provided for project-level notes. This has been set as the default Bookmarks folder in Project > Project Settings, so that when you create a new document from the Bookmarks sidebar in a Quick Reference panel, the document will be added to this folder.}
