\par\plain {\f1\fs36\b0\i0\cf3 Compiling}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Title pages and front matter are all provided in the \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Front Matter\u8221\'94 folder (between the \u8220\'93Places\u8221\'94 and \u8220\'93Notes\u8221\'94 folders). Different front matter is used for different formats.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\bullet 	}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Tip: You can open this document in a Quick Reference panel and have it open alongside the Compile panel if you need to refer to these instructions while compiling.}
